2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper uses a novel motion model to predict the motion of road-agents, which can be useful in robotics applications. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper uses a machine learning approach to track road-agents. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a novel motion model and tracking-by-detection approach, which involves machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely as the paper does not deal with cryptography or security, but it cannot be completely ruled out as the paper mentions collision avoidance, which can be related to security in some contexts.
